  "texts": [
    "Ferrag et al. [11] used BERT for threat detection in Internet of Things (IoT) networks, outperforming existing ML solutions by distinguishing between 14 attack classes and benign traffic using PCAP files.",
    "Alkhatib et al. [12] explored the usage of BERT for detecting threats on Controller Area Networks (CAN), showcasing the model's versatility across different cybersecurity applications.",
    "Among these, Chen et al. [13] is the only study which employed LLMs, which are pre-trained on natural language and possess a sequence-to-sequence head producing sequences of natural text tokens, to detect DDoS attacks by fine-tuning BERT.",
    "Explainable NIDSStudies aiming to render NIDS explainable typically employ existing explainable AI methods.",
    "These methods assign an importance factor to each input feature, indicating their influence on the model's output label [2]."
  ],
